public int pathSum(TreeNode root, int sum) {
	Map<Integer, Integer> preSum = new HashMap<>();
	preSum.put(0, 1);
	return helper(root, 0, sum ,preSum);
}

private int helper(TreeNode root, int curSum, int target, Map<Integer, Integer> preSum) {
	if(root == null) {
		return 0;
	}
	curSum += root.val;
	int res = preSum.getOrDefault(curSum - target, 0);
	preSum.put(curSum, preSum.getDefault(curSum, 0) + 1);
	res += helper(root.left, curSum, target, preSum) + helper(root.right, curSum, target, preSum);
	preSum.put(curSum, preSum.getDefault(curSum, 0) - 1);
	return res;
}


=> Binary Tree with parent pointers: A starts at root moving down, B starts at a leaf moving up. Scoring depends on who visits the nodes first.
Score can be full, zero, half if tie. Compute the maximum score A can collect.


Breakdown : 
root's parent = -1
We want to chose a leaf for B, that maximizes the total points collected by A, and return that maximum value.

suppose depth is D,
path : (root)v0 -> v1 -> ....vD (leaf)
A reaches node vi at time i
B reaches node vi at time D-i

if(i < D-i) OR i < D/2 -> A collects full point at vi 
if i = D-i & D is even -> A collects half
if i > D-i, A gets 0

full depth = floor((D-1)/2)

A points = sum(values[v0..v_full_depth]) + if(D is even then 0.5 * value[v_D/2]) else 0

we compute this for every leaf and then take the maximum


Algo: 
1. build adjacency list for parent pointers (undirected tree)
2. perform dfs from the root, keeping track of 
	a. depth of current node
	b. prefixSum[depth] = cumulative sum of nodes from root to current node
	c. pathNodes[depth] = node at that depth (for middle node when D is even)
3. When leaf is reached (no child), compute A_points
4. Update the global maximum
5. handle the trivial case N == 1 (root == leaf)

Code:

class RootLeafRace {
	
	double maxPoints = 0.0;
	int[] values;
	List<List<Integer>> tree;
	int root;
	int[] parent;
	int n; // no. of nodes

	public void maxPointsA() {

	// take input, if parent[i] == -1, root = i;

	// build undirected tree
	tree = new ArrayList<>;
	for(int i = 0;i<n;i++) tree.add(new ArrayList<>());
	for(int i =0;i<n;i++) {
		if(parent[i]!=-1) {
			tree.get(i).add(parent[i]);
			tree.get(parent[i]).add(i);
		}
	}

	// trivial case
	if(n==1) {
		maxPoints = values[0]/2.0;
		return;
	}

	// arrays for dfs
	int[] pathNodes = new int[n];
	double[] prefixSum = new double[n];

	dfs(root, -1, 0, pathNodes, prefixSum);

	sout(maxPoints);

	}

	void dfs(int node, int parent, int depth, int[] pathNodes, double[] prefixSum) {

		pathNodes[depth] = node;

		if(depth == 0) {
			prefixSum[depth] = values[node];
		} else {
			prefixSum[depth] = prefixSum[depth - 1] + values[node];
		}

		// check if this node is a leaf, means no children

		boolean isLeaf = true;

		for(int neighbor: tree.get(node)) {
			if(neighbor != parent) {
				isLeaf= false;
				dfs(neighbor, node, depth + 1, pathNodes, prefixSum);
			}
		}

		if(isLeaf) {
			int D = depth; // depth of this leaf

			// largest depth with full points: floor((D-1)/2)
			int fullDepth = (D-1)/2;
			double points = (fullDepth >= 0) ? prefixSum[fullDepth] : 0.0;

			if(D%2==0) { 
				int midDepth = D/2;
				points += 0.5 * values[pathNodes[midDepth]];
			}

			if(points > maxPoints) maxPoints = points;

		}


	}

}



