There are n riders and 1 car with infinite space. Each rider has a range of number of other riders that they are comfortable with. Ex: ith rider is comfortable with 3 to 5 other riders. If this condition is not met they do not ride in the car. Find out the maximum no of riders that is possible to fit in the car.

We have n riders and a car with infinite capacity. Each rider i has a comfort interval [L_i, R_i] representing the number of other riders they are comfortable with.
If the car contains k riders (including themselves), rider i is comfortable iff L_i <= k-1 <= R_i.
We want the maximum number of riders that can be in the car such that every rider in the car is comfortable.

==> sweep line or binary search problem => feasibility search type problem

n riders => each have range [l,r] to be comfortable => max number of rider so each is comfortable => find the intersection point which satisfys all conditions.



public int maxRiders(int n, int[][] ranges) {
	int diff = new int[n+2];
	for(int i = 0;i<n;i++) {
		int start = ranges[i][0];
		int end = ranges[i][1];
		if(start <= end) {
			diff[start] += 1;
			diff[end+1] -= 1;
		}
	}
	int count = 0;
	int answer = 0;
	for(int k = 1; k<=n; k++) {
		count += diff[k];
		if(count >= k) { 
			answer++;
		}
	}

	return answer;
} 

